                                                  <strong style="font-size: 17px; line-height: 20px;">October 6-8, 2017</strong><br />

                                                <td align="center"><a href="http://www.iaac.us/Literary-Festival2017/application-form.php" target="_blanck"><img src="http://www.iaac.us/newsletter/images/Third-Annual-IAAC-Literary-Festival.png" title="FOURTH ANNUAL IAAC LITERARY FESTIVAL" alt="FOURTH ANNUAL IAAC LITERARY FESTIVAL" /></a></td>

                                              <tr>
                                                <td align="left" style="padding: 0px 17px; text-align: lefft; font-size:16; line-height:20px;"> Are you an author? Is your heritage from the Indian subcontinent?<br />
                                                  <br />
                                                  The Indo-American Arts council is now accepting submissions for our third annual literary festival. We are looking for vibrant and thought-provoking literature in all genres. The IAAC is committed to the promotion of literary arts from the Indian Subcontinent(India, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, Nepal, Bhutan, Afghanistan). Our previously featured authors include Salman Rushdie, Madhur Jaffrey, Shashi Tharoor, Bapsi Sidwa, Javed Akhta

To publish a file:

   1. Open a file in Google Docs, Sheets, or Slides.
   2.  At the top, click File Publish to the web.
   3. The entire file will be published, but some file types have more             publishing options: ...
   4. Click Publish.
    5. Copy the URL and send it to anyone you'd like to see the file

yestaday I have done this image hover label issue solved by adding following code:

http://global-4pl.com/index.html                  


 <div id=""lables""> IOR/EOR</div>

.member-thumb .thumb-overlay {
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    height: 100%;
    opacity: 0;
    padding-left: 0;
    padding-top: 35%;  removed
    position: absolute;
    text-align: center;
    top: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    width: 100%;
}
#lables {
    color: #ffff00;
    display: block;
    left: 3px;
    position: relative;
    text-align: center !important;
    top: 98px;
}"

 To: Jigna[jignas] (WWD/ECLIPSE/192.168.1.105)
  at Fri Mar 31 15:08:25 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
Wednesday, May 3, 6.15 pm. Theater 3, Village East, NYC.
Buy Tickets

Shorts C - Comedy, Dance & Music
  	Cowboy and Indian
World Premiere
2016 | U S A | 8 mins | English
Directed By: Sujata Day
Cast: Sujata Day

Trailer: https://vimeo.com/201384724

Synopsis: A young Bengali bride, dressed head to toe in red bridal sari and dazzling jewels, materializes out of the barren, desert landscape like a mirage. Our Indian protagonist travels for miles on foot, fighting dehydration until she collapses in the dry heat. Hours pass, and a pickup truck parks next to her lifeless body. A cowboy hoists her up into his truck and drives off into the sunset. The frightened bride wakes up in the cowboys bedroom. The endearing cowboy attempts to talk to her, but gets nowhere because she doesnt speak English. The cowboy gives her privacy to shower and he takes a smoke break on his porch. Back in the cowboys bedroom, the cowboy tries again at communicating and they discover each others names, Kali and Clint. Kali breaks down crying and Clint comforts her. Suddenly, Kali slashes his throat. Clint falls to the ground, blood spurting out of his neck. Clints truck races away, with Kali at the wheel. Kali speaks perfect English into her cell, and assures the person on the other end of the line that theyre safe now. The truck speeds off into the desert sunrise.

About the Director: With her infectious personality and unique sense of humor, Pittsburgh native Sujata Day has established herself in Hollywood as a multi-talented actress, creator/writer, producer and director. She currently produces, writes, and stars in the dance sci-fi series Larry & Lucy. She honed her comedy skills at Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre, graduating from the improv program. Sujata is known for her starring role as CeCe in Issa Raes The Misadventures of Awkward Black Girl. Recent onscreen credits include a recurring role on HBOs Insecure, Brooklyn Nine-Nine, Life in Pieces and The Grinder. She is a 2016 Sundance | YouTube New Voices Lab fellow for her project Soda Shop. Sujata makes her narrative directing debut with the short film Cowboy and Indian. She is repped by 3 Arts Entertainment, Talentworks, and Myman Greenspan.

=====================================
 To: Sunil[Sunil] (IBS/DELL-1/192.168.1.83)
  at Sat May 13 13:04:00 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/6352293?utm_source=search_console&utm_campaign=sc-mft-test

Mobile-usability errors:

Flash usage

Most mobile browsers do not render Flash-based content. Therefore, mobile visitors will not be able to use a page that relies on Flash in order to display content, animations, or navigation. We recommend designing your look and feel and page animations using modern web technologies. Read more about Look and Feel in our Web Fundamentals guide.
Viewport not configured

Because visitors to your site use a variety of devices with varying screen sizesfrom large desktop monitors, to tablets and small smartphonesyour pages should specify a viewport using the meta viewport tag. This tag tells browsers how to adjust the pages dimension and scaling to suit the device. Learn more in Responsive Web Design Basics.
Fixed-width viewport

This report shows those pages with a viewport set to a fixed width. Some web developers define the viewport to a fixed pixel size in order to adjust a non-responsive page to suit common mobile screen sizes. To fix this error, adopt a responsive design for your sites pages, and set the viewport to match the devices width and scale accordingly. Read how to correctly Set the Viewport in our Web Fundamentals.
Content not sized to viewport

This report indicates pages where horizontal scrolling is necessary to see words and images on the page. This happens when pages use absolute values in CSS declarations, or use images designed to look best at a specific browser width (such as 980px). To fix this error, make sure the pages use relative width and position values for CSS elements, and make sure images can scale as well. Read more in Size Content to Viewport.
Small font size

This report identifies pages where the font size for the page is too small to be legible and would require mobile visitors to pinch to zoom in order to read. After specifying a viewport for your web pages, set your font sizes to scale properly within the viewport. Read more about font size best practices in Use Legible Font Sizes.
Touch elements too close

This report shows the URLs for sites where touch elements, such as buttons and navigational links, are so close to each other that a mobile user cannot easily tap a desired element with their finger without also tapping a neighboring element. To fix these errors, make sure to correctly size and space buttons and navigational links to be suitable for your mobile visitors. Read more in Size Tap Targets Appropriately.

 From: PankajB[PankajB] (QA/ANALYST/192.168.1.92)
  at Wed Jun 21 18:30:13 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
Origins of Palliative Care. 

Palliative care takes its roots from the modern hospice movement, which itself takes its origins only as recently as in 1967, when Dame Cicely Saunders, regarded as the founder of the modern hospice movement, founded St. Christopher's Hospice in the UK.

But today, Palliative care has developed far beyond the original hospice movement and is being seen as the third arm of medicine (preventative, curative and palliative)


=====================================

This testimonial came in last night.. It is rather nice and so we should try and include. 
 
Dear Devaunshi, I have headed back to London. Its been a gruelling couple of weeks but I do feel that my very dear Dad is finally at peace and with those he loved and waited so long to be with. Once again I cant thank you all enough for the peace you brought to his troubled mind in those last few months. I am sure this is what finally allowed him to let go and move on. I shall be eternally grateful for the help you extended to us. It really is beyond measure. 

Pesi Pestonjees daughter -  Nargis Walker 10 July 2017

MRF Tyres have been announced as the official tyre supplier for the CAMS Australian Rally Championship (ARC), Australia's national rally championship series. The Indian tyre manufacturer has signed a three-year deal as sole tyre supplier for the series, starting this year and extending to 2019. Helix Meeting Points - Added to doc
1. Mobile view - Slider images should be display like seen in desktop view.
2. Mobile view - Align in one line submenus with the main menu and highlight/differentiate main menus and submenus.
3. Mobile view - Bring Profile and menu icon/option at the right side.
4. Desktop/ Mobile view - Move up arrow to the right side below the FARM bar. Move little bit inside/left side the social icons.
5. Desktop/ Mobile view - Profile Cards/PROVIDER LIST - Message, Schedule Time, and Refer align text in one line.
6. Mobile view - HOW WE ASSIST Page Content - Differentiate content between all the sections. After Read More add line or use any other option
7. Desktop/ Mobile view - FIND SUPPORT -- DISCUSSION BOARD should go to the page http://helix.infobridgesolutions.com/helix-link-page/.
Same like footer menus/ page FAQ's, BLOG - Thank you for visiting Helix beta site!
8. Profile section - GENDER dropdown - Add new value as Transgender.

 To: Tauseef[TauseefM] (IBS/ASUS-1/192.168.1.139)
  at Fri Aug 18 14:29:52 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
>[Bug 3126] New: sliders at times appearing very faint or not loading (trying to see any pattern). Seem to become okay when scrolling down a bit and scrolling back up (screenshots attached)


solution:

update Page level css as below

inline 8

#min-range {
    float: left;
    width: 20%;
    text-align: left;
    color: #00bfd4;
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 26px;
}

inline 2
#slider-range {
	width: 60%;
	float: left;
	position: relative;
	top: 7px;
}

inline 18

#max-range {
	float: left;
	width: 20%;
	text-align: right;
	color: #00bfd4;
	font-size: 12px;
	line-height: 26px;
}

Tickets: $50; $45 IAAC members/NYU staff & faculty; $25 students w/ID BUY TICKETS

 From: Sunil[Sunil] (IBS/DELL-1/192.168.1.83)
  at Tue Aug 29 15:08:18 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
The United States is composed of and built by immigrants, and it has been a beacon to those in search of a new life for hundreds of years.    HOME is a collection of thirty-four poems and twelve songs inspired by a diverse group of immigrants who have made significant contributions to the United States. From Yo-Yo Ma to Audrey Hepburn, Albert Einstein to Celia Cruz, these poems symbolize the many roads that lead to America, and which we expect will continue to converge to build the highways to our future.    This unique collaboration takes the form of a keepsake hardcover book, with a CD of beautiful original music tucked inside. An audiobook edition in which Deepak Chopra reads the poems is also available, as a digital download. This hardcover book (with accompanying music CD) and digital-only audiobook will be available simultaneously in September 2017.


Offering a welcoming feeling intended to inform our cultural conversation and enhance our national dialogue, HOME has twelve accompanying musical pieces that serve as personal meditations on the essence of home, in which you can reflect upon where you feel most welcome, whether a place or state of mind.    Written and composed by immigrants and first generation Americans, HOME provides a stronger sense of welcome and belonging for everyone.

=====================================
 From: Sunil[Sunil] (IBS/DELL-1/192.168.1.117)
  at Wed Oct 11 17:12:38 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
Our lives are filled with challenges and uncertainty.
We are faced with decisions everyday that affect
us, our businesses and the ones we love. It's how
we approach those decisions that determine our
state of being. In his presentation, Ted shares The
Get To Principle; the ability to approach life from
the power of "I Get To" as opposed to the victim
feeling of "I have to".

"Our future is a wildcard. Our lives are filled with
strange challenges and uncertainties, which if
feared lead to resisting and controlling the future
before it happens and missing all the glory of the
present," says Ted. "Rather than argue with life
what if everything the future needs is given to us
this moment?"

"Businesses today are missing out on integrating
every experience on all levels, individual and
teams," asserts Ted. The principle helps businesses
see opportunities and have a shift of mind from
executive to explorer and adventurer and brings
the courage to connect more with the emerging
future possibilities offered by every experience. "


----

Ted Larkins is an accomplished business
executive and entrepreneur with a focus on
international licensing. In the 1990s Ted
co-developed a leading entertainment
licensing company in Tokyo, representing
major movie studios including Paramount
Pictures, Sony Pictures, and 20th Century
Fox. Hes worked on projects with Jon Bon
Jovi, Jack Nicklaus, Mariah Carey, Celine
Dion and many other artists. He is on the
board of directors of the Licensing Industry
Merchandise Association (LIMA), co-chairing
the charity committee and sitting on the
executive committee. He is a guest lecturer
for the UCLAx Entertainment Studies and
Performing Arts program.


He wrote the book, Get To Be Happy: Stories
and Secrets to Loving the Sh*t Out of Life over
the last year and a half during his daily,
4-hour train commute to work in Hollywood.
It will be on sale soon. Ted lives with his wife
of 22 years and their two children in
Southern California.

--

TO SCHEDULE PLEASE CONTACT:
Ted@TedLarkins.com
714-546-6266

--

"Rather than argue with life, what if everything
the future needs is given to us this moment?"

--
TEDLARKINS.COM

Thank you for confirming that nothing will go live just yet.


Regarding the updated pages, we have reviewed them & want to request the following edits to the homepage:


1) Please remove the attached photograph from the Slider Images - we no longer want to use it.


2) In the "A Wish Fulfilled" box:
a) Bring the photo of the patient with his family a bit lower down Or just lengthen it a bit- we feel this will make the text wrapping better.


b) Change the copy from:
"Recently, PALCARE put in an extra effort to help fulfil the last wish of a young patient." (when we say extra effort it seems only on occasion that we put in an extra effort, so this is misleading)
TO

"In October 2017, PALCARE, along with V Care Foundation, fulfilled the last wish of a young patient."


c) Add a full-stop at the end of the last sentence "Recently, PALCARE put in an extra effort to help fulfil the last wish of a young patient."




3) In the "Transforming Lives" box, add a full-stop at the end of the last sentence "We provide a few of their stories."




4) In the "Our Medical Team" box, add a full-stop at the end of the sentence "The heartbeat of our organization comprises an interdisciplinary team of specially trained doctors, nurses, psychologists, social workers."


5) In the "What our patient families say", add a closed parentheses at the end of the quote "No medical team has ever explained the treatment plan and everything related to Charanjits illness so properly "


6) In the "Remembering Loved Ones" box, we feel that having the title and then the "Remebrance Day" underneath is a bit redundant.
SO, LET US DO IT THIS WAY - change copy to:
"On the 1st of December each year  our Remembrance Day -  PALCARE commemorates patients who have passed away in the preceding 12 months, by sending their families a diya to light up on that day."
 
Also, add a full-stop at the end of the sentence " On the 1st of December each year, PALCARE commemorates patients who have passed away in the preceding 12 months, by sending their families a diya to light up on that day."


7) The Donations box at the bottom left could stand out a bit more - do a green background with white font just like for the "Our Medical Team" box.


Let us know if anything isn't clear.

Thank you for confirming that nothing will go live just yet.


Regarding the updated pages, we have reviewed them & want to request the following edits to the homepage:


1) Please remove the attached photograph from the Slider Images - we no longer want to use it.


2) In the "A Wish Fulfilled" box:
a) Bring the photo of the patient with his family a bit lower down Or just lengthen it a bit- we feel this will make the text wrapping better.


b) Change the copy from:
"Recently, PALCARE put in an extra effort to help fulfil the last wish of a young patient." (when we say extra effort it seems only on occasion that we put in an extra effort, so this is misleading)
TO

"In October 2017, PALCARE, along with V Care Foundation, fulfilled the last wish of a young patient."


c) Add a full-stop at the end of the last sentence "Recently, PALCARE put in an extra effort to help fulfil the last wish of a young patient."




3) In the "Transforming Lives" box, add a full-stop at the end of the last sentence "We provide a few of their stories."




4) In the "Our Medical Team" box, add a full-stop at the end of the sentence "The heartbeat of our organization comprises an interdisciplinary team of specially trained doctors, nurses, psychologists, social workers."


5) In the "What our patient families say", add a closed parentheses at the end of the quote "No medical team has ever explained the treatment plan and everything related to Charanjits illness so properly "


6) In the "Remembering Loved Ones" box, we feel that having the title and then the "Remebrance Day" underneath is a bit redundant.
SO, LET US DO IT THIS WAY - change copy to:
"On the 1st of December each year  our Remembrance Day -  PALCARE commemorates patients who have passed away in the preceding 12 months, by sending their families a diya to light up on that day."
 
Also, add a full-stop at the end of the sentence " On the 1st of December each year, PALCARE commemorates patients who have passed away in the preceding 12 months, by sending their families a diya to light up on that day."


7) The Donations box at the bottom left could stand out a bit more - do a green background with white font just like for the "Our Medical Team" box.


Let us know if anything isn't clear.

 From: Shrutika[shrutikar] (METRO/ASP/192.168.1.130)
  at Tue Nov 28 12:06:23 2017 (RSA)(sealed)
-------------------------------------
1. JPEG or JPG: Joint Photographic Experts Group (graphics file compression standard)
2. MPEG : Moving Picture Experts Group (defines compression standards)
3. GIF: Graphic Interchange Format
4.PNG: Portable Network Graphics (Comparatively better then JPEG and support binary transparency and alpha channel transparency)
5. AVI  Stands for Audio Video Interleaved, storing sound and moving pictures in RIFF format developed by Microsoft
6. DVD  DVD once stood for Digital Video Disc or Digital Versatile Disc, but now it just stands for DVD  the next generation of optical disc storage technology. DVD is essentially a bigger, faster CD that can hold cinema-like video, better-than-CD audio, and computer data.
7. WMV  Windows Media file with Audio and/or Video (WMV):
